FBIS4-39454 "drsov110_a_94031" FBIS-SOV-94-110 Daily Report 8 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Memorandum of Understanding Signed With OAS Memorandum of Understanding Signed With OAS LD0806114194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0653 GMT 8 Jun 94 LD0806114194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Chistov] [Summary] Brasilia, 8 Jun -- Russia has signed a memorandum of mutual understanding with the Organization of American States (OAS). Russia has been a permanent observer with the OAS since 1982. The memorandum sets the guidelines for cooperation between Russia and the OAS. Russia Deputy Foreign Minister Georgiy Mamedov, who signed the memorandum on Russia's behalf, also delivered to the OAS general secretary, Juao Clemente Baena Soares, a message from the Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev.
